translated: Broek, Sven Josef, former export inspection veterinarian, former district veterinarian, born February 24, 1882 in Falkenberg to district veterinarian A. J. Andersson and Aurora Borgström. Married in 1909 to Elin Stenström. Children: Sven-Åke, born in 1910 and working as a bank clerk in Karlstad; Ingegärd, born in 1912 and married to office veterinarian Inge Lauritzen, employed in the Medical Corps; Anita, born in 1913 and married to a civilian engineer and pilot named Hans Enderlein in Östersund; Margareta, born in 1915 and working in insurance in Stockholm; Per Olof, born in 1917 and working as a butler in Gävle; Gunnar, born in 1919 and working as an engineer at the General Engineering Bureau in Karlstad; Lennart, born in 1921 and working as an engineer at Johnsonkoncernen in Nynäshamn; and Nils, born in 1926 and practicing forestry in Falkenberg. Received a high school diploma in 1901 and a veterinary degree in 1906. District veterinarian in Ullared in 1907 and in Falkenberg in 1908 until retirement. Export inspection veterinarian 1910-1946. Private veterinary practice since 1946. Recipient of the Royal Order of Vasa, 1st class and Halland's Household Society's gold medal. Married.
